         <div xml:id="vicavKeyboards">
            <head>Keyboard Layouts for our Transcription</head>
            <p>We have created installable keyboard layouts for Windows using
               the <ref target="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=102134">
                  Microsoft Keyboard Layout Creator</ref>. We can offer them for
               German keyboards (y &amp;lt;-&amp;gt; z Position). They are inspired by DMG
               transcription. There is a Writer document in the archives that
               shows how it works. For Mac OSX we found SIL's
               <ref target="http://scripts.sil.org/cms/scripts/page.php?site_id=nrsi&amp;amp;id=ukelele">
                  Ukulele</ref> very useful.</p>
            <p>
               <ref target="https://minerva.arz.oeaw.ac.at/static/vicavarz.zip">Keyboard</ref>
               for transcribing Egyptian Arabic or Modern Standard Arabic in VICAV
               transcription (' -&amp;gt; ʔ, ʿ -&amp;gt; ʕ)</p>
            <p>
               <ref target="https://minerva.arz.oeaw.ac.at/static/vicavapc.zip">Keyboard</ref>
               for transcribing Damascene Arabic (ž &amp;lt;-&amp;gt; ǧ)</p>
            <p>
               <ref target="https://minerva.arz.oeaw.ac.at/static/victuerw.zip">Keyboard</ref>
               for transcribing Tunisian Arabic</p>
         </div>

